decision_conditions: The use hereby permitted shall be discontinued and the land restored to its former condition on or before 31 August 2023

Reason: In order that the local planning authority may assess the impact of the use at the end of the limited period hereby permitted, having regard to any complaints received and any other material considerations existing at the time, and to comply with section 8 of the National Planning Policy Framework(2021), policy 7B of the Ealing Development Management Development Plan 2013, policy 1.1 (g) of the Ealing Development (Core) Strategy 2012 and policies S1 and S3 of the London Plan(2021) | The development hereby approved shall be carried out in accordance with drawing title number(s): Unnumbered plan titled Location plan; Unnumbered plan titled Existing site plan; Unnumbered plan titled Proposed site plan; Unnumbered plan titled Proposed GA plan; Unnumbered plan titled Proposed roof plan; Unnumbered plan titled Proposed elevations
Reason: For the avoidance of doubt, and in the interests of proper planning.

| All external materials to be used in the development shall match those indicated on the approved plans or application form . Development shall be carried out in accordance with the approved details.

Reason: To ensure that the materials harmonise with the surroundings, in accordance with policies 1.1 & 1.2 of the Ealing Core Strategy (2012), policies 7.4 & 7B of the Ealing Development Management Development Plan Document (2013), London Plan(2021) policies D1, D3 and D4 and the National Planning Policy Framework (2021).
description: Construction of a temporary  (until August 2023)  single storey building to be used as exam/drama hall.
